Transcription.Text: As well as strong naturally-characteristic individual variations, this includes a midnight sinking and a dawn rise. At high light intensities the animals keep station at their optimum by a vertical hop-and-sink behavior and this confirms earlier observations on station-keeping in Balanus nauplii.
